//! gg-walker-wasm — Tier-C "interpreter-embed" walker for GG orchestration
//! topologies (Betti → WASM Phase 5 Tier C).
//!
//! # What this is
//!
//! All ~20 polyglot languages lower to the GG topology IR **at build time on
//! the host** (`gnosis_polyglot::parse_and_extract_orchestration`; tree-sitter
//! never crosses into wasm). This crate is the small wasm32 runtime that
//! executes the **property-carried subset** of that IR — nodes whose semantics
//! ride entirely in `labels` + `properties` (`callee`, `expr`, `args`, `bind`,
//! literals, foil fork/fold edge annotations) with **no source re-parse**.
//! Everything outside that subset TRAPS fail-closed (`WalkError` natively; a
//! real wasm trap via `panic = "abort"` under wasm32), so the wasm lane never
//! answers where it could disagree with the gnexec walker.
//!
//! # Input envelope
//!
//! The walker cdylib is identical across programs; the topology rides in the
//! json-v1 input instead of a data segment (data-segment splicing of a
//! `gnosis-gg-topology` custom section is documented future work — a cdylib
//! cannot read its own custom sections, so splicing would require patching
//! the data section at package time). The json-v1 input bytes MUST be one of
//! two versioned shapes — exactly these keys, nothing else:
//!
//! **envelope v1** (single self-contained topology):
//!
//! ```json
//! { "topology": { ...GgTopology JSON... }, "input": <program input> }
//! ```
//!
//! **envelope v2** (topology + the helper topologies its certified call
//! graph needs — source-borne programs like `echo.ts` whose exported
//! function calls other extracted functions):
//!
//! ```json
//! { "topology": { ... }, "helpers": { "<fn name>": { ...GgTopology... } }, "input": <program input> }
//! ```
//!
//! `helpers` maps a callee name (the `callee` property of a call node) to
//! that function's own extracted `GgTopology`. An empty `helpers` object is
//! valid v2 and means exactly what v1 means. The host packager
//! (`gnosis_polyglot::aot_gg_embed`) emits a `<artifactId>.topology.json`
//! sidecar and pins its hash in the manifest (`topologyHash`); for v2
//! programs the sidecar is the wrapper `{"topology": …, "helpers": …}`, for
//! v1 programs it stays the bare topology JSON (byte-identical to the
//! pre-helpers contract).
//!
//! **envelope v3** (bounded-step / resumable walks — Wave C of the sovereign
//! compute fabric; design doc
//! `open-source/x-gnosis/docs/BETTI_STATEFUL_TELEPORT_DESIGN.md`) adds two
//! OPTIONAL keys; v1/v2 envelopes are byte-compatible and behave exactly as
//! before:
//!
//! ```json
//! { "topology": {…}, "helpers": {…}, "input": …, "budget": N, "resume": <cursor> }
//! ```
//!
//! - `budget` (non-negative integer): a HOP budget for this invocation. When
//!   the walk would exceed it, instead of trapping, `main` COMPLETES with a
//!   JSON cursor — `{"__gg_cursor__": {"nodeId", "frames", "pending",
//!   "ordinal", "topo"}}` — the serializable walk state at a node boundary
//!   (`frames` = the root→innermost frame stack, each `{t, nodeId, scope,
//!   pending}`; `ordinal` = total hops consumed so far, monotone across
//!   suspensions; `topo` = fnv1a-64 fingerprint of the canonical
//!   topology+helpers, so a cursor can never resume against a different
//!   program).
//! - `resume` (a previously returned cursor): continues the walk from that
//!   state. The envelope MUST carry the same topology, helpers, and input
//!   the cursor was suspended under (the fingerprint pins the program; the
//!   input is the caller's obligation, exactly like re-running).
//!
//! Cursors exist ONLY at certified node boundaries — every value they carry
//! (scope bindings, pending fold results) is already JSON by construction.
//! Anything outside the certified subset traps exactly as an unbounded walk
//! would, budget or not (fail closed; a cursor is never minted for a node
//! the walker cannot classify).
//!
//! # v2 certified coverage (verified against gnexec — see tests)
//!
//! Node labels the walker recognizes, and ONLY these:
//!
//! - `Entry` / `PolyglotBridgeEntry` — entry marker. The walk starts at the
//!   unique Entry-labeled node with no incoming `Process` edge. If the entry
//!   carries `param_names` (a JSON array of strings), the walk binds them:
//!   the ROOT topology may declare at most ONE parameter, bound to the
//!   program input (gnexec `--input-json` semantics); helper topologies bind
//!   each parameter to the evaluated call argument, positionally.
//! - `Statement` / `PolyglotBridgeStatement` / `PolyglotBridgeCall` — a call
//!   statement. The callee must be one of:
//!   - `Promise.all` with a `bind_pattern`, backed by explicit foil edges
//!     (`FORK`/`FOLD` with `foil_lowering: "Promise.all"`,
//!     `scheduler: "gnosis-foil"` — the same recognizer gnexec's
//!     `topology_has_promise_all_fork_fold_candidate` uses). Branch nodes
//!     (`Branch`/`FoilBranch` + `PolyglotBridgeCall`) run in `branch_index`
//!     order through the certified builtin table below.
//!   - `merge` with a `bind` — folds the pending fork results with `"|"`
//!     (gnexec `try_foil_fanout_user_id_hot` semantics).
//!   - a **user-defined helper**: `callee` names a topology in the envelope's
//!     `helpers` map. The node must carry `args` (a JSON array of certified
//!     argument IR — `literal` / `ident` / `member`), arity must equal the
//!     helper's `param_names` length, and the certified call graph must be
//!     ACYCLIC (recursion declines at package time and traps at run time).
//!     The helper's return value binds to the node's `bind` name when
//!     present, and is discarded otherwise. Helper names shadowing the
//!     certified builtins (`Promise.all`, `merge`, `loadUser`,
//!     `loadProfile`) decline — ambiguous.
//! - `Return` / `PolyglotBridgeReturn` — evaluates the property-carried
//!   `expr` (see below) and ends the walk.
//! - `Join` / `PolyglotBridgeJoin` — consumed by the certified fork/fold
//!   execution; stepping ONTO one via a `Process` edge is a decline.
//! - `TsBridgeEntry` / `TsBridgeCall` / `TsBridgeReturn` — property-free
//!   pass-through markers (the checked-in `echo.gg` shape). gnexec walks
//!   these as no-ops and yields `null`; so does the walker. Any properties
//!   on them → decline.
//!
//! Certified branch builtins (gnexec's foil fanout semantics, exact):
//! `loadUser(userId) = "<userId>:user"`, `loadProfile(userId) =
//! "<userId>:profile"`, applied to the REQUIRED string input field `userId`.
//! A non-string or missing `userId` declines (gnexec stringifies non-string
//! ids; the walker traps instead — trapping where the reference answers is
//! safe, answering differently is not).
//!
//! `expr` forms the walker evaluates (Return nodes and call arguments):
//! - bare identifier (`summary`) — local binding lookup;
//! - `input.<field>` — root input object field (string form; helper frames
//!   have no root input, so this form declines inside helpers);
//! - single/double-quoted literal (`'hello'`) — string literal, no escapes;
//! - canonical-IR JSON:
//!   - `{"kind":"literal","value":<json>}` — the value;
//!   - `{"kind":"ident","name":"x"}` — local binding lookup (parameters are
//!     bound at frame entry via `param_names`);
//!   - `{"kind":"member","obj":{"kind":"ident","name":"o"},"prop":"f"}` —
//!     field access on a bound object; missing field declines;
//!   - `{"kind":"template","parts":[{"kind":"text","s":"…"},
//!     {"kind":"expr","e":<ir>}]}` — template-literal concatenation.
//!     **String-only in this version**: every `expr` part must evaluate to a
//!     JSON string; numbers/null/objects TRAP (gnexec would stringify —
//!     decline-not-divergence).
//! Anything else — every other IR kind, including `call` in expression
//! position and `binary` — declines. There is NO general expression
//! evaluation here (loops/arithmetic are Tier A's compiled lane).
//!
//! Edge types: `Process` (single-successor step), `Fork`/`Fold` (only as the
//! certified foil pair). `Race`, `Vent`, `Interfere` or any unknown edge
//! type → decline at load.

use std::collections::BTreeMap;

use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use serde_json::Value;

#[cfg(target_arch = "wasm32")]
mod wasm;

/// Hop budget: fail closed instead of spinning if a topology walks in
/// circles. The certified subset is loop-free, so any topology that
/// legitimately needs more hops is outside the subset anyway.
const MAX_HOPS: usize = 4096;

/// Call-depth backstop for user-defined helper calls. The certified call
/// graph is statically acyclic, so depth is bounded by the helper count;
/// this cap is belt-and-suspenders against validator drift.
const MAX_CALL_DEPTH: usize = 32;

/// Callee names owned by the certified builtin machinery; a helper topology
/// under one of these names is ambiguous and declines.
const RESERVED_CALLEES: [&str; 4] = ["Promise.all", "merge", "loadUser", "loadProfile"];

// ── Minimal serde mirror of gnosis_polyglot::gg_compiler::GgTopology ──
//
// Deliberately NOT a dependency on gnosis-polyglot (which cannot build for
// wasm32: tree-sitter grammars are C). Field names/shapes mirror the serde
// output of `GgTopology`; unknown fields (`source_map`, `metadata`,
// `source_span`, …) are ignored — they carry provenance, not semantics.

// Serialize exists ONLY for the cursor fingerprint (`program_fingerprint`):
// serializing the PARSED mirror normalizes provenance-only fields
// (`source_map`, `metadata`, …) away, so the fingerprint covers semantics.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct Topology {
    pub nodes: Vec<Node>,
    pub edges: Vec<Edge>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct Node {
    pub id: String,
    pub labels: Vec<String>,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub properties: BTreeMap<String, String>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct Edge {
    pub source_ids: Vec<String>,
    pub target_ids: Vec<String>,
    /// Serde variant name of `GgEdgeType`: "Process" | "Fork" | "Fold" | …
    #[serde(rename = "type")]
    pub edge_type: String,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub properties: BTreeMap<String, String>,
}

/// The envelope's helper map: callee name → that function's topology.
pub type Helpers = BTreeMap<String, Topology>;

/// A walker decline. Under wasm32 this becomes a real trap (`panic!` with
/// `panic = "abort"` lowers to `unreachable`); natively it is a `Result` so
/// the host emitter can preflight and tests can assert fail-closure.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub struct WalkError(pub String);

impl std::fmt::Display for WalkError {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "gg-walker decline: {}", self.0)
    }
}

impl std::error::Error for WalkError {}

fn decline<T>(msg: impl Into<String>) -> Result<T, WalkError> {
    Err(WalkError(msg.into()))
}

// ── Cursors (envelope v3) ────────────────────────────────────────────

/// The one key a suspended walk's result object carries.
pub const GG_CURSOR_KEY: &str = "__gg_cursor__";

/// How a bounded walk ended: ran to completion, or suspended with a cursor
/// (the JSON value `{"__gg_cursor__": {…}}` a later `resume` continues).
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum WalkOutcome {
    Complete(Value),
    Suspended(Value),
}

/// One entry of the cursor's frame stack (root → innermost). The innermost
/// frame's node is ABOUT TO EXECUTE; every outer frame's node is the
/// in-flight user-helper call the walk is suspended inside.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
struct CursorFrame {
    /// `"root"` or `"helper:<name>"`.
    tag: String,
    node_id: String,
    scope: BTreeMap<String, Value>,
    pending: Option<Vec<Value>>,
}

/// Internal walk signal: a decline (trap) or a suspension unwinding with the
/// frame stack collected root-first.
#[derive(Debug)]
enum WalkSignal {
    Decline(WalkError),
    Suspend(Vec<CursorFrame>),
}

impl From<WalkError> for WalkSignal {
    fn from(e: WalkError) -> Self {
        WalkSignal::Decline(e)
    }
}

fn signal_decline<T>(msg: impl Into<String>) -> Result<T, WalkSignal> {
    Err(WalkSignal::Decline(WalkError(msg.into())))
}

/// Hop accounting shared across every frame of one invocation. `remaining`
/// is the envelope's `budget` (None = unbounded, never suspends); `ordinal`
/// is the TOTAL hops consumed across the walk's whole life — it starts from
/// the resume cursor's ordinal, so it is strictly monotone across
/// suspensions (the replay/rollback anchor of the stateful teleport lane).
struct Budget {
    remaining: Option<u64>,
    ordinal: u64,
}

/// fnv1a-64 over the canonical serialization of the PARSED program
/// (topology + helpers). Pins a cursor to the program it was suspended
/// under; deliberately dependency-free (same fingerprint family as the
/// betti `artifactId`).
fn fnv1a64(bytes: &[u8]) -> u64 {
    let mut hash: u64 = 0xcbf29ce484222325;
    for byte in bytes {
        hash ^= u64::from(*byte);
        hash = hash.wrapping_mul(0x100000001b3);
    }
    hash
}

fn program_fingerprint(topology: &Topology, helpers: &Helpers) -> String {
    let repr = serde_json::to_string(&(topology, helpers))
        .expect("parsed program mirrors are always serializable");
    format!("{:016x}", fnv1a64(repr.as_bytes()))
}

fn build_cursor(frames: &[CursorFrame], ordinal: u64, fingerprint: &str) -> Value {
    let frames_json: Vec<Value> = frames
        .iter()
        .map(|frame| {
            serde_json::json!({
                "t": frame.tag,
                "nodeId": frame.node_id,
                "scope": frame.scope,
                "pending": frame.pending,
            })
        })
        .collect();
    let innermost = frames.last().expect("a suspension has at least one frame");
    let inner = serde_json::json!({
        "nodeId": innermost.node_id,
        "frames": frames_json,
        "pending": innermost.pending,
        "ordinal": ordinal,
        "topo": fingerprint,
    });
    let mut outer = serde_json::Map::new();
    outer.insert(GG_CURSOR_KEY.to_string(), inner);
    Value::Object(outer)
}

/// Fail-closed cursor parse: exact key discipline, fingerprint pinning,
/// frame-tag/helper cross-checks, innermost-duplication consistency.
fn parse_cursor(
    raw: &Value,
    helpers: &Helpers,
    fingerprint: &str,
) -> Result<(Vec<CursorFrame>, u64), WalkError> {
    let Some(outer) = raw.as_object() else {
        return decline("resume cursor must be a JSON object");
    };
    if outer.len() != 1 || !outer.contains_key(GG_CURSOR_KEY) {
        return decline(format!(
            "resume cursor must carry exactly the '{GG_CURSOR_KEY}' key"
        ));
    }
    let Some(cursor) = outer[GG_CURSOR_KEY].as_object() else {
        return decline(format!("'{GG_CURSOR_KEY}' must be a JSON object"));
    };
    for key in cursor.keys() {
        if !matches!(
            key.as_str(),
            "nodeId" | "frames" | "pending" | "ordinal" | "topo"
        ) {
            return decline(format!("cursor carries unknown key '{key}'"));
        }
    }
    let Some(topo) = cursor.get("topo").and_then(Value::as_str) else {
        return decline("cursor has no 'topo' program fingerprint");
    };
    if topo != fingerprint {
        return decline(format!(
            "cursor 'topo' fingerprint {topo} does not match this program's \
             {fingerprint} — a cursor never resumes against a different \
             topology (fail closed)"
        ));
    }
    let Some(ordinal) = cursor.get("ordinal").and_then(Value::as_u64) else {
        return decline("cursor 'ordinal' must be a non-negative integer");
    };
    let Some(frames_raw) = cursor.get("frames").and_then(Value::as_array) else {
        return decline("cursor 'frames' must be a non-empty array");
    };
    if frames_raw.is_empty() {
        return decline("cursor 'frames' must be a non-empty array");
    }
    let mut frames = Vec::with_capacity(frames_raw.len());
    for (index, raw_frame) in frames_raw.iter().enumerate() {
        let Some(obj) = raw_frame.as_object() else {
            return decline(format!("cursor frames[{index}] must be an object"));
        };
        for key in obj.keys() {
            if !matches!(key.as_str(), "t" | "nodeId" | "scope" | "pending") {
                return decline(format!(
                    "cursor frames[{index}] carries unknown key '{key}'"
                ));
            }
        }
        let Some(tag) = obj.get("t").and_then(Value::as_str) else {
            return decline(format!("cursor frames[{index}] has no string 't'"));
        };
        if index == 0 {
            if tag != "root" {
                return decline(format!(
                    "cursor frames[0] tag '{tag}' must be 'root'"
                ));
            }
        } else {
            let Some(name) = tag.strip_prefix("helper:") else {
                return decline(format!(
                    "cursor frames[{index}] tag '{tag}' must be 'helper:<name>'"
                ));
            };
            if !helpers.contains_key(name) {
                return decline(format!(
                    "cursor frames[{index}] names helper '{name}' which this \
                     envelope does not carry"
                ));
            }
        }
        let Some(node_id) = obj.get("nodeId").and_then(Value::as_str) else {
            return decline(format!("cursor frames[{index}] has no string 'nodeId'"));
        };
        let scope: BTreeMap<String, Value> = match obj.get("scope") {
            Some(Value::Object(map)) => map
                .iter()
                .map(|(k, v)| (k.clone(), v.clone()))
                .collect(),
            _ => {
                return decline(format!(
                    "cursor frames[{index}] 'scope' must be a JSON object"
                ))
            }
        };
        let pending = match obj.get("pending") {
            None | Some(Value::Null) => None,
            Some(Value::Array(items)) => Some(items.clone()),
            Some(_) => {
                return decline(format!(
                    "cursor frames[{index}] 'pending' must be null or an array"
                ))
            }
        };
        frames.push(CursorFrame {
            tag: tag.to_string(),
            node_id: node_id.to_string(),
            scope,
            pending,
        });
    }
    let innermost = frames.last().expect("non-empty");
    if cursor.get("nodeId").and_then(Value::as_str) != Some(innermost.node_id.as_str()) {
        return decline("cursor 'nodeId' disagrees with the innermost frame");
    }
    let dup_pending = cursor.get("pending").cloned().unwrap_or(Value::Null);
    let inner_pending = match &innermost.pending {
        None => Value::Null,
        Some(items) => Value::Array(items.clone()),
    };
    if dup_pending != inner_pending {
        return decline("cursor 'pending' disagrees with the innermost frame");
    }
    Ok((frames, ordinal))
}

// ── Envelope ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/// Parse the json envelope — `{"topology": …, "input": …}` (v1),
/// `{"topology": …, "helpers": {…}, "input": …}` (v2), or the v3 superset
/// with optional `budget`/`resume` (see crate docs) — run the walker, and
/// return the result serialized as JSON text. A bounded walk that runs out
/// of budget COMPLETES with the cursor JSON as its result (not a trap).
pub fn run_envelope_bytes(bytes: &[u8]) -> Result<String, WalkError> {
    let envelope: Value = match serde_json::from_slice(bytes) {
        Ok(v) => v,
        Err(e) => return decline(format!("envelope is not valid JSON: {e}")),
    };
    let Some(obj) = envelope.as_object() else {
        return decline("envelope must be a JSON object");
    };
    for key in obj.keys() {
        if !matches!(
            key.as_str(),
            "topology" | "helpers" | "input" | "budget" | "resume"
        ) {
            return decline(format!(
                "envelope key '{key}' is outside the contract — v1 \
                 (topology, input), v2 (+ helpers), v3 (+ optional budget, \
                 resume)"
            ));
        }
    }
    if !obj.contains_key("topology") || !obj.contains_key("input") {
        return decline(
            "envelope must carry at least the keys 'topology' and 'input'",
        );
    }
    let topology: Topology = match serde_json::from_value(obj["topology"].clone()) {
        Ok(t) => t,
        Err(e) => return decline(format!("topology does not deserialize: {e}")),
    };
    let helpers = match obj.get("helpers") {
        None => Helpers::new(),
        Some(h) => parse_helpers(h)?,
    };
    let budget = match obj.get("budget") {
        None => None,
        Some(v) => match v.as_u64() {
            Some(n) => Some(n),
            None => {
                return decline(
                    "envelope 'budget' must be a non-negative integer hop budget",
                )
            }
        },
    };
    let outcome = run_program_bounded(
        &topology,
        &helpers,
        &obj["input"],
        budget,
        obj.get("resume"),
    )?;
    let result = match outcome {
        WalkOutcome::Complete(value) => value,
        WalkOutcome::Suspended(cursor) => cursor,
    };
    match serde_json::to_string(&result) {
        Ok(s) => Ok(s),
        Err(e) => decline(format!("result does not serialize: {e}")),
    }
}

fn parse_helpers(helpers: &Value) -> Result<Helpers, WalkError> {
    let Some(map) = helpers.as_object() else {
        return decline("'helpers' must be a JSON object mapping callee name → topology");
    };
    let mut out = Helpers::new();
    for (name, topo) in map {
        let topology: Topology = match serde_json::from_value(topo.clone()) {
            Ok(t) => t,
            Err(e) => {
                return decline(format!("helper '{name}' does not deserialize: {e}"))
            }
        };
        out.insert(name.clone(), topology);
    }
    Ok(out)
}

/// Static (input-free) validation that a SINGLE topology (no helpers) is
/// inside the walker's certified subset. Kept for v1 hosts; equivalent to
/// `validate_program` with an empty helper map.
pub fn validate_topology(topology: &Topology) -> Result<(), WalkError> {
    validate_program(topology, &Helpers::new())
}

/// `validate_topology` over raw JSON — convenience for hosts that hold a v1
/// (bare-topology) sidecar.
pub fn validate_topology_json(topology_json: &str) -> Result<(), WalkError> {
    let topology: Topology = match serde_json::from_str(topology_json) {
        Ok(t) => t,
        Err(e) => return decline(format!("topology does not deserialize: {e}")),
    };
    validate_topology(&topology)
}

/// Static admission over a full program: the root topology plus its helper
/// topologies. This is what the host packager runs at package time; every
/// input-free decline the runtime would hit is caught here (labels, edge
/// types, callees, foil fork/fold shape, `expr`/`args` IR forms, helper
/// arity, call-graph acyclicity). Input-dependent declines (missing input
/// fields, unbound identifiers, non-string template parts) remain runtime
/// traps.
pub fn validate_program(topology: &Topology, helpers: &Helpers) -> Result<(), WalkError> {
    for reserved in RESERVED_CALLEES {
        if helpers.contains_key(reserved) {
            return decline(format!(
                "helper name '{reserved}' shadows a certified builtin; ambiguous"
            ));
        }
    }

    // Root topology: structural + reachable-walk admission.
    let root_graph = Graph::build(topology)?;
    let root_calls = root_graph.validate_statically(helpers)?;
    let root_params = entry_param_names(&topology.nodes[root_graph.entry])?;
    if root_params.len() > 1 {
        return decline(format!(
            "root topology declares {} parameters; the program input binds at \
             most one",
            root_params.len()
        ));
    }

    // Helpers: every provided helper must itself admit (fail closed even if
    // unreached), with parseable params.
    let mut calls_by_caller: BTreeMap<&str, Vec<UserCall>> = BTreeMap::new();
    let mut param_count: BTreeMap<&str, usize> = BTreeMap::new();
    for (name, helper) in helpers {
        let graph = Graph::build(helper).map_err(|e| {
            WalkError(format!("helper '{name}': {}", e.0))
        })?;
        let calls = graph.validate_statically(helpers).map_err(|e| {
            WalkError(format!("helper '{name}': {}", e.0))
        })?;
        let params = entry_param_names(&helper.nodes[graph.entry]).map_err(|e| {
            WalkError(format!("helper '{name}': {}", e.0))
        })?;
        param_count.insert(name.as_str(), params.len());
        calls_by_caller.insert(name.as_str(), calls);
    }

    // Arity: every certified call site matches its helper's parameter count.
    for call in root_calls
        .iter()
        .chain(calls_by_caller.values().flatten())
    {
        let expected = param_count[call.callee.as_str()];
        if call.argc != expected {
            return decline(format!(
                "call node '{}' passes {} args to '{}' which takes {}",
                call.node_id, call.argc, call.callee, expected
            ));
        }
    }

    // Acyclicity of the helper call graph (recursion → decline). The root
    // cannot be called back into (it has no callee name), so cycles can only
    // form among helpers.
    detect_call_cycle(&calls_by_caller)
}

/// `validate_program` over the sidecar text a host holds. Accepts BOTH
/// sidecar shapes: a bare `GgTopology` JSON (v1) or the program wrapper
/// `{"topology": …, "helpers": {…}}` (v2, exactly those two keys).
pub fn validate_program_json(sidecar_json: &str) -> Result<(), WalkError> {
    let value: Value = match serde_json::from_str(sidecar_json) {
        Ok(v) => v,
        Err(e) => return decline(format!("sidecar is not valid JSON: {e}")),
    };
    let is_wrapper = value
        .as_object()
        .is_some_and(|obj| obj.len() == 2 && obj.contains_key("topology") && obj.contains_key("helpers"));
    if is_wrapper {
        let topology: Topology = match serde_json::from_value(value["topology"].clone()) {
            Ok(t) => t,
            Err(e) => return decline(format!("topology does not deserialize: {e}")),
        };
        let helpers = parse_helpers(&value["helpers"])?;
        validate_program(&topology, &helpers)
    } else {
        let topology: Topology = match serde_json::from_value(value) {
            Ok(t) => t,
            Err(e) => return decline(format!("topology does not deserialize: {e}")),
        };
        validate_topology(&topology)
    }
}

/// Depth-first cycle detection over the helper→helper call edges.
fn detect_call_cycle(calls_by_caller: &BTreeMap<&str, Vec<UserCall>>) -> Result<(), WalkError> {
    #[derive(Clone, Copy, PartialEq)]
    enum Color {
        White,
        Gray,
        Black,
    }
    fn visit(
        name: &str,
        calls_by_caller: &BTreeMap<&str, Vec<UserCall>>,
        colors: &mut BTreeMap<String, Color>,
    ) -> Result<(), WalkError> {
        match colors.get(name).copied().unwrap_or(Color::White) {
            Color::Gray => {
                return decline(format!(
                    "recursive certified call graph through '{name}'; recursion is \
                     outside the property-carried subset"
                ))
            }
            Color::Black => return Ok(()),
            Color::White => {}
        }
        colors.insert(name.to_string(), Color::Gray);
        if let Some(calls) = calls_by_caller.get(name) {
            for call in calls {
                visit(&call.callee, calls_by_caller, colors)?;
            }
        }
        colors.insert(name.to_string(), Color::Black);
        Ok(())
    }
    let mut colors: BTreeMap<String, Color> = BTreeMap::new();
    for name in calls_by_caller.keys() {
        visit(name, calls_by_caller, &mut colors)?;
    }
    Ok(())
}

/// Parse an Entry node's `param_names` property (JSON array of strings).
/// Absent → no parameters (the checked-in `.gg` fixture shape). Present but
/// unparseable → decline.
fn entry_param_names(entry: &Node) -> Result<Vec<String>, WalkError> {
    match entry.properties.get("param_names") {
        None => Ok(Vec::new()),
        Some(raw) => match serde_json::from_str::<Vec<String>>(raw) {
            Ok(names) => Ok(names),
            Err(e) => decline(format!(
                "entry node '{}' has unparseable 'param_names': {e}",
                entry.id
            )),
        },
    }
}

// ── Graph preparation (everything here is a load-time decline) ───────

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
enum NodeKind {
    Entry,
    Call,
    Return,
    Join,
    /// Certified fork branch — executed by the fork/fold arm, never stepped
    /// onto via Process edges.
    Branch,
    /// Property-free Ts bridge marker (echo.gg shape): walk-through no-op.
    PassThrough,
}

fn classify(node: &Node) -> Result<NodeKind, WalkError> {
    let has = |l: &str| node.labels.iter().any(|x| x == l);
    // Branch first: foil branches carry PolyglotBridgeCall AND Branch/FoilBranch.
    if (has("FoilBranch") || has("Branch")) && has("PolyglotBridgeCall") {
        return Ok(NodeKind::Branch);
    }
    if has("Entry") || has("PolyglotBridgeEntry") {
        return Ok(NodeKind::Entry);
    }
    if has("Return") || has("PolyglotBridgeReturn") {
        return Ok(NodeKind::Return);
    }
    if has("Join") || has("PolyglotBridgeJoin") {
        return Ok(NodeKind::Join);
    }
    if has("Statement") || has("PolyglotBridgeStatement") || has("PolyglotBridgeCall") {
        return Ok(NodeKind::Call);
    }
    if node
        .labels
        .iter()
        .all(|l| matches!(l.as_str(), "TsBridgeEntry" | "TsBridgeCall" | "TsBridgeReturn"))
        && !node.labels.is_empty()
    {
        if !node.properties.is_empty() {
            return decline(format!(
                "bridge marker node '{}' carries properties; semantics unknown",
                node.id
            ));
        }
        return Ok(NodeKind::PassThrough);
    }
    decline(format!(
        "node '{}' has no certified label (labels: {:?})",
        node.id, node.labels
    ))
}

/// A statically-discovered call to a user-defined helper.
struct UserCall {
    callee: String,
    argc: usize,
    node_id: String,
}

struct Graph<'t> {
    topology: &'t Topology,
    /// node index by id
    by_id: BTreeMap<&'t str, usize>,
    /// Classification is evaluated per node but only ENFORCED on touch: a
    /// node the walk never reaches (e.g. fanout.gg's audit-only `Trace`
    /// sink) cannot affect the output, and gnexec likewise ignores it.
    /// Stepping onto — or fork/folding through — an uncertified node
    /// declines.
    kinds: Vec<Result<NodeKind, WalkError>>,
    entry: usize,
}

impl<'t> Graph<'t> {
    /// Structural admission: ids, edge types, and the unique root entry.
    /// Reachable-walk semantics are checked by `validate_statically`.
    fn build(topology: &'t Topology) -> Result<Graph<'t>, WalkError> {
        if topology.nodes.is_empty() {
            return decline("topology has no nodes");
        }
        let mut by_id: BTreeMap<&str, usize> = BTreeMap::new();
        for (i, n) in topology.nodes.iter().enumerate() {
            if by_id.insert(n.id.as_str(), i).is_some() {
                return decline(format!("duplicate node id '{}'", n.id));
            }
        }
        let kinds: Vec<Result<NodeKind, WalkError>> =
            topology.nodes.iter().map(classify).collect();
        for e in &topology.edges {
            match e.edge_type.as_str() {
                "Process" | "Fork" | "Fold" => {}
                other => {
                    return decline(format!(
                        "edge type '{other}' is outside the certified subset (Process/Fork/Fold)"
                    ))
                }
            }
            if e.source_ids.is_empty() || e.target_ids.is_empty() {
                return decline("edge with empty source_ids or target_ids");
            }
            for id in e.source_ids.iter().chain(e.target_ids.iter()) {
                if !by_id.contains_key(id.as_str()) {
                    return decline(format!("edge references unknown node id '{id}'"));
                }
            }
        }

        // Entry: the unique Entry-labeled node with no incoming Process edge.
        let mut entries = Vec::new();
        for (i, n) in topology.nodes.iter().enumerate() {
            if kinds[i] != Ok(NodeKind::Entry) {
                continue;
            }
            let has_incoming = topology.edges.iter().any(|e| {
                e.edge_type == "Process" && e.target_ids.iter().any(|t| t == &n.id)
            });
            if !has_incoming {
                entries.push(i);
            }
        }
        let entry = match entries.as_slice() {
            [one] => *one,
            [] => return decline("no root Entry node (Entry label, no incoming Process edge)"),
            _ => return decline("multiple root Entry nodes; ambiguous"),
        };

        Ok(Graph {
            topology,
            by_id,
            kinds,
            entry,
        })
    }

    /// Classification of node `idx`, enforced at touch time.
    fn kind(&self, idx: usize) -> Result<NodeKind, WalkError> {
        self.kinds[idx].clone()
    }

    /// Input-free admission sweep: every node REACHABLE on the Process walk
    /// must have executable (or pass-through) semantics, and every Call node
    /// must be a certified builtin — or a user-defined helper present in
    /// `helpers`, whose call sites are returned for program-level arity and
    /// acyclicity checks.
    fn validate_statically(&self, helpers: &Helpers) -> Result<Vec<UserCall>, WalkError> {
        let mut calls = Vec::new();
        let mut current = self.entry;
        let mut hops = 0usize;
        loop {
            hops += 1;
            if hops > MAX_HOPS {
                return decline(format!("walk exceeded {MAX_HOPS} hops"));
            }
            let node = &self.topology.nodes[current];
            match self.kind(current)? {
                NodeKind::Entry | NodeKind::PassThrough => {}
                NodeKind::Call => {
                    match node.properties.get("callee").map(String::as_str) {
                        Some("Promise.all") => {
                            self.certified_fork_fold(current)?;
                        }
                        Some("merge") => {
                            if !node.properties.contains_key("bind") {
                                return decline(format!(
                                    "merge node '{}' has no 'bind' property",
                                    node.id
                                ));
                            }
                        }
                        Some(name) if helpers.contains_key(name) => {
                            calls.push(validate_user_call(node, name)?);
                        }
                        Some(other) => {
                            return decline(format!(
                                "callee '{other}' is outside the certified builtin set \
                                 and has no helper topology"
                            ))
                        }
                        None => {
                            return decline(format!(
                                "call node '{}' carries no 'callee' property",
                                node.id
                            ))
                        }
                    }
                }
                NodeKind::Return => {
                    let Some(expr) = node.properties.get("expr") else {
                        return decline(format!(
                            "return node '{}' has no property-carried 'expr'",
                            node.id
                        ));
                    };
                    validate_expr_form(expr)?;
                    return Ok(calls);
                }
                NodeKind::Join => {
                    return decline(format!(
                        "Process walk stepped onto Join node '{}'; joins are only \
                         consumed by the certified fork/fold",
                        node.id
                    ))
                }
                NodeKind::Branch => {
                    return decline(format!(
                        "Process walk stepped onto fork branch '{}'",
                        node.id
                    ))
                }
            }
            match self.process_successor(current)? {
                Some(next) => current = next,
                None => return Ok(calls), // walk falls off the end → null
            }
        }
    }

    /// The single Process successor of `idx`, or None at the end of the walk.
    /// More than one outgoing Process edge (or a multi-target Process edge)
    /// is ambiguous → decline.
    fn process_successor(&self, idx: usize) -> Result<Option<usize>, WalkError> {
        let id = &self.topology.nodes[idx].id;
        let mut successors = Vec::new();
        for e in &self.topology.edges {
            if e.edge_type != "Process" || !e.source_ids.iter().any(|s| s == id) {
                continue;
            }
            for t in &e.target_ids {
                successors.push(self.by_id[t.as_str()]);
            }
        }
        match successors.as_slice() {
            [] => Ok(None),
            [one] => Ok(Some(*one)),
            _ => {
                // The checked-in fanout.gg join has two audit Process edges
                // (TUNNEL/MEASURE lowered to Process) — but we never STEP from
                // the join. Anywhere the actual walk faces >1 successor the
                // program is ambiguous for a property-carried walker.
                decline(format!("node '{id}' has multiple Process successors; ambiguous"))
            }
        }
    }

    /// Locate + shape-check the certified foil fork/fold pair rooted at the
    /// `Promise.all` statement node. Mirrors the explicit-edge arm of
    /// gnexec's `topology_has_promise_all_fork_fold_candidate`.
    fn certified_fork_fold(&self, stmt_idx: usize) -> Result<ForkFold<'t>, WalkError> {
        let stmt = &self.topology.nodes[stmt_idx];
        let Some(bind_pattern) = stmt.properties.get("bind_pattern") else {
            return decline(format!(
                "Promise.all node '{}' has no 'bind_pattern'",
                stmt.id
            ));
        };

        let is_foil = |props: &BTreeMap<String, String>| {
            props.get("foil_lowering").map(String::as_str) == Some("Promise.all")
                && props.get("scheduler").map(String::as_str) == Some("gnosis-foil")
        };

        let mut forks = self.topology.edges.iter().filter(|e| {
            e.edge_type == "Fork" && e.source_ids.iter().any(|s| s == &stmt.id) && is_foil(&e.properties)
        });
        let Some(fork) = forks.next() else {
            return decline(format!(
                "Promise.all node '{}' has no explicit foil Fork edge",
                stmt.id
            ));
        };
        if forks.next().is_some() {
            return decline(format!("multiple foil Fork edges from '{}'", stmt.id));
        }
        // Width >= 1: a one-armed Promise.all is semantically sound and is
        // exactly what the mesh scheduler ships to a station — the
        // coordinator splits an N-arm fork into N width-1 sub-topologies
        // (x-gnosis mesh-schedule.ts) and re-applies the merge fold, so
        // arm-level walks must certify. Zero-width forks stay declined.
        if fork.target_ids.is_empty() {
            return decline("foil Fork edge needs >= 1 branch target");
        }
        if let Some(branches) = stmt.properties.get("branches") {
            if branches.parse::<usize>().ok() != Some(fork.target_ids.len()) {
                return decline(format!(
                    "'branches' property ({branches}) disagrees with Fork targets ({})",
                    fork.target_ids.len()
                ));
            }
        }

        let mut fork_targets: Vec<&str> = fork.target_ids.iter().map(String::as_str).collect();
        fork_targets.sort_unstable();
        let mut folds = self.topology.edges.iter().filter(|e| {
            if e.edge_type != "Fold" || !is_foil(&e.properties) {
                return false;
            }
            let mut sources: Vec<&str> = e.source_ids.iter().map(String::as_str).collect();
            sources.sort_unstable();
            sources == fork_targets
        });
        let Some(fold) = folds.next() else {
            return decline(format!(
                "no foil Fold edge folding the Fork branches of '{}'",
                stmt.id
            ));
        };
        if folds.next().is_some() {
            return decline(format!("multiple foil Fold edges for '{}'", stmt.id));
        }
        let [join_id] = fold.target_ids.as_slice() else {
            return decline("foil Fold edge must target exactly one Join node");
        };
        let join_idx = self.by_id[join_id.as_str()];
        if self.kind(join_idx)? != NodeKind::Join {
            return decline(format!("Fold target '{join_id}' is not a Join node"));
        }
        let join = &self.topology.nodes[join_idx];
        if join.properties.get("bind_pattern") != Some(bind_pattern) {
            return decline(format!(
                "Join '{join_id}' bind_pattern disagrees with statement '{}'",
                stmt.id
            ));
        }
        if let Some(arity) = join.properties.get("arity") {
            if arity.parse::<usize>().ok() != Some(fork.target_ids.len()) {
                return decline(format!("Join '{join_id}' arity disagrees with Fork width"));
            }
        }

        // Branches: certified builtins, ordered by branch_index.
        let mut branches: Vec<(usize, &'t Node)> = Vec::new();
        for target in &fork.target_ids {
            let idx = self.by_id[target.as_str()];
            if self.kind(idx)? != NodeKind::Branch {
                return decline(format!("fork target '{target}' is not a certified branch"));
            }
            let node = &self.topology.nodes[idx];
            let Some(index) = node
                .properties
                .get("branch_index")
                .and_then(|v| v.parse::<usize>().ok())
            else {
                return decline(format!("branch '{target}' has no parseable 'branch_index'"));
            };
            let callee = node.properties.get("callee").map(String::as_str);
            if !matches!(callee, Some("loadUser") | Some("loadProfile")) {
                return decline(format!(
                    "branch '{target}' callee {callee:?} is outside the certified builtin set"
                ));
            }
            branches.push((index, node));
        }
        branches.sort_by_key(|(index, _)| *index);
        if branches
            .windows(2)
            .any(|pair| pair[0].0 == pair[1].0)
        {
            return decline("duplicate branch_index in fork branches");
        }

        Ok(ForkFold {
            bind_pattern: bind_pattern.clone(),
            branches: branches.into_iter().map(|(_, node)| node).collect(),
        })
    }
}

/// Static shape check of a user-helper call node: `args` must be a JSON
/// array of certified argument IR forms.
fn validate_user_call(node: &Node, callee: &str) -> Result<UserCall, WalkError> {
    let Some(raw_args) = node.properties.get("args") else {
        return decline(format!(
            "call node '{}' (callee '{callee}') carries no 'args' property",
            node.id
        ));
    };
    let parsed: Value = match serde_json::from_str(raw_args) {
        Ok(v) => v,
        Err(e) => {
            return decline(format!(
                "call node '{}' has unparseable 'args': {e}",
                node.id
            ))
        }
    };
    let Some(args) = parsed.as_array() else {
        return decline(format!("call node '{}' 'args' is not a JSON array", node.id));
    };
    for arg in args {
        validate_ir_form(arg)?;
    }
    Ok(UserCall {
        callee: callee.to_string(),
        argc: args.len(),
        node_id: node.id.clone(),
    })
}

struct ForkFold<'t> {
    bind_pattern: String,
    branches: Vec<&'t Node>,
}

// ── Execution ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/// Walk a single self-contained topology (no helpers) over `input`.
/// Equivalent to `run_program` with an empty helper map.
pub fn run_topology(topology: &Topology, input: &Value) -> Result<Value, WalkError> {
    run_program(topology, &Helpers::new(), input)
}

/// Walk the program (root topology + helpers) over `input` and produce the
/// result. Runs the full static admission first — so recursion, unknown
/// callees, and malformed shapes trap here at run time exactly as they
/// decline at package time — then executes. Every unsupported shape is a
/// `WalkError` (a trap under wasm32).
pub fn run_program(
    topology: &Topology,
    helpers: &Helpers,
    input: &Value,
) -> Result<Value, WalkError> {
    match run_program_bounded(topology, helpers, input, None, None)? {
        WalkOutcome::Complete(value) => Ok(value),
        WalkOutcome::Suspended(_) => {
            decline("unreachable: an unbounded walk cannot suspend")
        }
    }
}

/// Bounded/resumable walk (envelope v3). `budget` is the hop budget for THIS
/// invocation (None = unbounded); `resume` is a cursor a previous bounded
/// invocation of the SAME program returned. Suspension is a normal outcome,
/// never a trap; every decline stays a `WalkError` exactly as in
/// [`run_program`].
pub fn run_program_bounded(
    topology: &Topology,
    helpers: &Helpers,
    input: &Value,
    budget: Option<u64>,
    resume: Option<&Value>,
) -> Result<WalkOutcome, WalkError> {
    validate_program(topology, helpers)?;
    let fingerprint = program_fingerprint(topology, helpers);

    let mut budget_state = Budget {
        remaining: budget,
        ordinal: 0,
    };
    let resume_frames: Option<Vec<CursorFrame>> = match resume {
        None => None,
        Some(raw) => {
            let (frames, ordinal) = parse_cursor(raw, helpers, &fingerprint)?;
            budget_state.ordinal = ordinal;
            Some(frames)
        }
    };

    // Root frame: `input.<field>` resolves against the program input, and
    // the root's single declared parameter (if any) binds to it. On resume
    // the cursor's saved scope replaces this fresh binding.
    let graph = Graph::build(topology)?;
    let params = entry_param_names(&topology.nodes[graph.entry])?;
    let mut scope: BTreeMap<String, Value> = BTreeMap::new();
    if let [name] = params.as_slice() {
        scope.insert(name.clone(), input.clone());
    }
    match exec_frame_bounded(
        topology,
        helpers,
        scope,
        input,
        0,
        &mut budget_state,
        "root",
        resume_frames.as_deref(),
    ) {
        Ok(value) => Ok(WalkOutcome::Complete(value)),
        Err(WalkSignal::Decline(e)) => Err(e),
        Err(WalkSignal::Suspend(frames)) => Ok(WalkOutcome::Suspended(build_cursor(
            &frames,
            budget_state.ordinal,
            &fingerprint,
        ))),
    }
}

/// Execute one frame (the root topology or one helper invocation).
/// `frame_input` is what the `input.<field>` string form resolves against:
/// the program input in the root frame, `null` in helper frames (helpers
/// see only their bound parameters — any `input.` access there declines).
///
/// Bounded-step semantics: each loop iteration is one HOP. Before executing
/// a node, an exhausted budget suspends — the node is NOT executed and
/// becomes the cursor's innermost `nodeId`, so resume re-enters exactly
/// there. `resume_path` (root→innermost cursor frames) restores this frame's
/// state and, when deeper frames exist, fast-forwards through the in-flight
/// helper call WITHOUT re-evaluating its arguments (the callee frame's saved
/// scope already carries the bound parameters).
#[allow(clippy::too_many_arguments)]
fn exec_frame_bounded(
    topology: &Topology,
    helpers: &Helpers,
    fresh_scope: BTreeMap<String, Value>,
    frame_input: &Value,
    depth: usize,
    budget: &mut Budget,
    frame_tag: &str,
    resume_path: Option<&[CursorFrame]>,
) -> Result<Value, WalkSignal> {
    if depth > MAX_CALL_DEPTH {
        return signal_decline(format!("call depth exceeded {MAX_CALL_DEPTH}"));
    }
    let graph = Graph::build(topology)?;
    let mut scope = fresh_scope;
    let mut pending_fold: Option<Vec<Value>> = None;
    let mut current = graph.entry;
    let mut descend: Option<&[CursorFrame]> = None;

    if let Some(path) = resume_path {
        let (frame, rest) = path.split_first().expect("parse_cursor: non-empty");
        if frame.tag != frame_tag {
            return signal_decline(format!(
                "cursor frame tag '{}' does not match execution frame '{frame_tag}'",
                frame.tag
            ));
        }
        let Some(&idx) = graph.by_id.get(frame.node_id.as_str()) else {
            return signal_decline(format!(
                "cursor references unknown node id '{}'",
                frame.node_id
            ));
        };
        // Only certified node kinds are resume positions (fail closed).
        graph.kind(idx)?;
        scope = frame.scope.clone();
        pending_fold = frame.pending.clone();
        current = idx;
        if !rest.is_empty() {
            descend = Some(rest);
        }
    }

    // Suspension helper: prepend THIS frame's state to the unwinding stack.
    let suspend_through = |frames: &mut Vec<CursorFrame>,
                           node_id: &str,
                           scope: &BTreeMap<String, Value>,
                           pending: &Option<Vec<Value>>| {
        frames.insert(
            0,
            CursorFrame {
                tag: frame_tag.to_string(),
                node_id: node_id.to_string(),
                scope: scope.clone(),
                pending: pending.clone(),
            },
        );
    };

    let mut hops = 0usize;
    loop {
        hops += 1;
        if hops > MAX_HOPS {
            return signal_decline(format!("walk exceeded {MAX_HOPS} hops"));
        }
        let node = &topology.nodes[current];

        if let Some(rest) = descend.take() {
            // Fast-forward: this node is the IN-FLIGHT user-helper call the
            // cursor suspended inside. Its hop was consumed before the
            // original suspension; do not charge it again.
            if graph.kind(current)? != NodeKind::Call {
                return signal_decline(format!(
                    "cursor descends through node '{}' which is not a call node",
                    node.id
                ));
            }
            let Some(callee) = node.properties.get("callee") else {
                return signal_decline(format!(
                    "cursor descends through call node '{}' with no callee",
                    node.id
                ));
            };
            let expected_tag = format!("helper:{callee}");
            if rest[0].tag != expected_tag {
                return signal_decline(format!(
                    "cursor descends into frame '{}' but node '{}' calls '{callee}'",
                    rest[0].tag, node.id
                ));
            }
            let Some(helper) = helpers.get(callee.as_str()) else {
                return signal_decline(format!(
                    "cursor descends into helper '{callee}' which this envelope \
                     does not carry"
                ));
            };
            let result = match exec_frame_bounded(
                helper,
                helpers,
                BTreeMap::new(),
                &Value::Null,
                depth + 1,
                budget,
                &expected_tag,
                Some(rest),
            ) {
                Ok(value) => value,
                Err(WalkSignal::Suspend(mut frames)) => {
                    suspend_through(&mut frames, &node.id, &scope, &pending_fold);
                    return Err(WalkSignal::Suspend(frames));
                }
                Err(other) => return Err(other),
            };
            if let Some(bind) = node.properties.get("bind") {
                scope.insert(bind.clone(), result);
            }
        } else {
            // Certified-kind gate FIRST: a node the walker cannot classify
            // declines (traps) exactly as an unbounded walk would — a cursor
            // is never minted for it.
            let kind = graph.kind(current)?;
            if budget.remaining == Some(0) {
                return Err(WalkSignal::Suspend(vec![CursorFrame {
                    tag: frame_tag.to_string(),
                    node_id: node.id.clone(),
                    scope,
                    pending: pending_fold,
                }]));
            }
            if let Some(remaining) = budget.remaining.as_mut() {
                *remaining -= 1;
            }
            budget.ordinal += 1;
            match kind {
                NodeKind::Entry | NodeKind::PassThrough => {}
                NodeKind::Call => match node.properties.get("callee").map(String::as_str) {
                    Some("Promise.all") => {
                        let fork_fold = graph.certified_fork_fold(current)?;
                        let mut results = Vec::with_capacity(fork_fold.branches.len());
                        for branch in &fork_fold.branches {
                            results.push(run_certified_builtin(branch, frame_input)?);
                        }
                        scope.insert(
                            fork_fold.bind_pattern.clone(),
                            Value::Array(results.clone()),
                        );
                        pending_fold = Some(results);
                    }
                    Some("merge") => {
                        let Some(parts) = pending_fold.take() else {
                            return signal_decline(format!(
                                "merge node '{}' has no pending fork/fold results",
                                node.id
                            ));
                        };
                        let mut strings = Vec::with_capacity(parts.len());
                        for part in &parts {
                            match part {
                                Value::String(s) => strings.push(s.as_str()),
                                other => {
                                    return signal_decline(format!(
                                        "merge over non-string fold result: {other}"
                                    ))
                                }
                            }
                        }
                        let Some(bind) = node.properties.get("bind") else {
                            return signal_decline(format!(
                                "merge node '{}' has no 'bind' property",
                                node.id
                            ));
                        };
                        scope.insert(bind.clone(), Value::String(strings.join("|")));
                    }
                    Some(name) if helpers.contains_key(name) => {
                        let result = match call_user_helper_bounded(
                            node,
                            name,
                            helpers,
                            &scope,
                            frame_input,
                            depth,
                            budget,
                        ) {
                            Ok(value) => value,
                            Err(WalkSignal::Suspend(mut frames)) => {
                                suspend_through(&mut frames, &node.id, &scope, &pending_fold);
                                return Err(WalkSignal::Suspend(frames));
                            }
                            Err(other) => return Err(other),
                        };
                        if let Some(bind) = node.properties.get("bind") {
                            scope.insert(bind.clone(), result);
                        }
                        // No bind → the (pure) helper's result is discarded,
                        // matching gnexec's bare-call statement semantics.
                    }
                    Some(other) => {
                        return signal_decline(format!(
                            "callee '{other}' is outside the certified builtin set \
                             and has no helper topology"
                        ))
                    }
                    None => {
                        return signal_decline(format!(
                            "call node '{}' carries no 'callee' property",
                            node.id
                        ))
                    }
                },
                NodeKind::Return => {
                    return Ok(eval_return(node, &scope, frame_input)?);
                }
                NodeKind::Join | NodeKind::Branch => {
                    return signal_decline(format!(
                        "Process walk stepped onto '{}' (join/branch nodes are only \
                         consumed by the certified fork/fold)",
                        node.id
                    ));
                }
            }
        }
        match graph.process_successor(current)? {
            Some(next) => current = next,
            None => return Ok(Value::Null), // fell off the end (echo.gg shape)
        }
    }
}

/// Evaluate a user-defined helper call: eval the argument IR in the CALLER
/// frame, bind the helper's parameters positionally, and walk the helper
/// topology as a fresh frame (whose `input.` form resolves against `null` —
/// helpers only see their parameters).
fn call_user_helper_bounded(
    node: &Node,
    callee: &str,
    helpers: &Helpers,
    caller_scope: &BTreeMap<String, Value>,
    caller_input: &Value,
    depth: usize,
    budget: &mut Budget,
) -> Result<Value, WalkSignal> {
    let call = validate_user_call(node, callee)?;
    let raw_args = node.properties.get("args").expect("validated");
    let arg_irs: Vec<Value> = match serde_json::from_str::<Value>(raw_args) {
        Ok(Value::Array(items)) => items,
        _ => {
            return signal_decline(format!(
                "call node '{}' 'args' is not a JSON array",
                node.id
            ))
        }
    };
    let mut argv = Vec::with_capacity(arg_irs.len());
    for ir in &arg_irs {
        argv.push(eval_ir(ir, caller_scope, caller_input)?);
    }

    let helper = &helpers[callee];
    let graph = Graph::build(helper)?;
    let params = entry_param_names(&helper.nodes[graph.entry])?;
    if params.len() != call.argc {
        return signal_decline(format!(
            "call node '{}' passes {} args to '{callee}' which takes {}",
            node.id,
            call.argc,
            params.len()
        ));
    }
    let mut scope: BTreeMap<String, Value> = BTreeMap::new();
    for (name, value) in params.iter().zip(argv) {
        scope.insert(name.clone(), value);
    }
    exec_frame_bounded(
        helper,
        helpers,
        scope,
        &Value::Null,
        depth + 1,
        budget,
        &format!("helper:{callee}"),
        None,
    )
}

/// The certified branch builtin table — gnexec's foil fanout semantics
/// (`try_foil_fanout_user_id_hot`), exactly:
/// `loadUser(u) = "<u>:user"`, `loadProfile(u) = "<u>:profile"` over the
/// REQUIRED string input field `userId`.
fn run_certified_builtin(branch: &Node, input: &Value) -> Result<Value, WalkError> {
    let Some(user_id) = input.get("userId").and_then(Value::as_str) else {
        return decline(
            "certified fanout requires a string 'userId' input field \
             (non-string ids decline; gnexec would stringify)",
        );
    };
    match branch.properties.get("callee").map(String::as_str) {
        Some("loadUser") => Ok(Value::String(format!("{user_id}:user"))),
        Some("loadProfile") => Ok(Value::String(format!("{user_id}:profile"))),
        other => decline(format!("branch callee {other:?} has no certified builtin")),
    }
}

fn eval_return(node: &Node, scope: &BTreeMap<String, Value>, input: &Value) -> Result<Value, WalkError> {
    let Some(expr) = node.properties.get("expr") else {
        return decline(format!(
            "return node '{}' has no property-carried 'expr'",
            node.id
        ));
    };
    eval_expr(expr, scope, input)
}

fn is_bare_ident(s: &str) -> bool {
    let mut chars = s.chars();
    match chars.next() {
        Some(c) if c.is_ascii_alphabetic() || c == '_' => {}
        _ => return false,
    }
    chars.all(|c| c.is_ascii_alphanumeric() || c == '_')
}

/// Input-free shape check of an `expr` property: is it one of the certified
/// forms at all? (Bindings and input fields stay runtime checks.) Used by
/// the static admission sweep so the host emitter declines un-walkable
/// returns at package time.
fn validate_expr_form(expr: &str) -> Result<(), WalkError> {
    if let Ok(ir) = serde_json::from_str::<Value>(expr) {
        return match &ir {
            Value::Object(_) => validate_ir_form(&ir),
            Value::String(_) => Ok(()),
            other => decline(format!("expr JSON '{other}' has no certified meaning")),
        };
    }
    if let Some(field) = expr.strip_prefix("input.") {
        if is_bare_ident(field) {
            return Ok(());
        }
        return decline(format!("input member path '{expr}' is not a plain field"));
    }
    if expr.len() >= 2 && expr.starts_with('\'') && expr.ends_with('\'') {
        let inner = &expr[1..expr.len() - 1];
        if inner.contains('\'') || inner.contains('\\') {
            return decline(format!("string literal '{expr}' has uncertified escapes"));
        }
        return Ok(());
    }
    if is_bare_ident(expr) {
        return Ok(());
    }
    decline(format!(
        "expression '{expr}' is outside the property-carried subset"
    ))
}

/// Input-free shape check of a canonical-IR JSON value — the certified
/// kinds: `literal`, `ident`, `member` (over a bound ident), `template`
/// (text/expr parts). `call` in EXPRESSION position, `binary`, and every
/// other kind decline.
fn validate_ir_form(ir: &Value) -> Result<(), WalkError> {
    let Some(obj) = ir.as_object() else {
        return decline(format!("IR '{ir}' is not a JSON object"));
    };
    match obj.get("kind").and_then(Value::as_str) {
        Some("literal") => {
            if obj.get("value").is_some() {
                Ok(())
            } else {
                decline("literal IR without 'value'")
            }
        }
        Some("ident") => {
            if obj.get("name").and_then(Value::as_str).is_some() {
                Ok(())
            } else {
                decline("ident IR without string 'name'")
            }
        }
        Some("member") => {
            let Some(prop) = obj.get("prop").and_then(Value::as_str) else {
                return decline("member IR without string 'prop'");
            };
            if !is_bare_ident(prop) {
                return decline(format!("member IR prop '{prop}' is not a plain field"));
            }
            let Some(inner) = obj.get("obj") else {
                return decline("member IR without 'obj'");
            };
            // v1: only member-of-bound-ident (e.g. `input.name`); deeper
            // chains and computed objects are outside the subset.
            if inner.get("kind").and_then(Value::as_str) == Some("ident")
                && inner.get("name").and_then(Value::as_str).is_some()
            {
                Ok(())
            } else {
                decline(format!(
                    "member IR object '{inner}' is not a plain identifier"
                ))
            }
        }
        Some("template") => {
            let Some(parts) = obj.get("parts").and_then(Value::as_array) else {
                return decline("template IR without 'parts' array");
            };
            for part in parts {
                match part.get("kind").and_then(Value::as_str) {
                    Some("text") => {
                        if part.get("s").and_then(Value::as_str).is_none() {
                            return decline("template text part without string 's'");
                        }
                    }
                    Some("expr") => {
                        let Some(e) = part.get("e") else {
                            return decline("template expr part without 'e'");
                        };
                        validate_ir_form(e)?;
                    }
                    other => {
                        return decline(format!(
                            "template part kind {other:?} is outside the certified subset"
                        ))
                    }
                }
            }
            Ok(())
        }
        Some("call") => decline(
            "call IR in expression position is outside the certified subset \
             (certified calls are statement-level 'callee'/'args' nodes)",
        ),
        Some(kind) => decline(format!(
            "IR kind '{kind}' is outside the property-carried subset"
        )),
        None => decline("expr JSON object without 'kind'"),
    }
}

/// Property-carried expression evaluation — the FULL certified grammar. No
/// general expression or JS evaluation lives here; anything else declines.
fn eval_expr(
    expr: &str,
    scope: &BTreeMap<String, Value>,
    input: &Value,
) -> Result<Value, WalkError> {
    // Canonical-IR JSON (extractor-emitted `expr` payloads).
    if let Ok(ir) = serde_json::from_str::<Value>(expr) {
        return match &ir {
            Value::Object(_) => eval_ir(&ir, scope, input),
            // A JSON string expr is a quoted literal.
            Value::String(s) => Ok(Value::String(s.clone())),
            other => decline(format!("expr JSON '{other}' has no certified meaning")),
        };
    }

    // input.<field>
    if let Some(field) = expr.strip_prefix("input.") {
        if !is_bare_ident(field) {
            return decline(format!("input member path '{expr}' is not a plain field"));
        }
        return match input.get(field) {
            Some(v) => Ok(v.clone()),
            None => decline(format!("input has no field '{field}'")),
        };
    }

    // 'single-quoted literal' (no escapes, no interior quotes)
    if expr.len() >= 2 && expr.starts_with('\'') && expr.ends_with('\'') {
        let inner = &expr[1..expr.len() - 1];
        if inner.contains('\'') || inner.contains('\\') {
            return decline(format!("string literal '{expr}' has uncertified escapes"));
        }
        return Ok(Value::String(inner.to_string()));
    }

    // bare identifier → local binding
    if is_bare_ident(expr) {
        return match scope.get(expr) {
            Some(v) => Ok(v.clone()),
            None => decline(format!("unbound identifier '{expr}'")),
        };
    }

    decline(format!(
        "expression '{expr}' is outside the property-carried subset"
    ))
}

/// Evaluate a canonical-IR JSON value: `literal` / `ident` / `member` /
/// `template` (string-only concatenation). Everything else declines.
fn eval_ir(
    ir: &Value,
    scope: &BTreeMap<String, Value>,
    input: &Value,
) -> Result<Value, WalkError> {
    validate_ir_form(ir)?;
    let obj = ir.as_object().expect("validated");
    match obj.get("kind").and_then(Value::as_str) {
        Some("literal") => Ok(obj.get("value").expect("validated").clone()),
        Some("ident") => {
            let name = obj["name"].as_str().expect("validated");
            match scope.get(name) {
                Some(v) => Ok(v.clone()),
                None => decline(format!("unbound identifier '{name}'")),
            }
        }
        Some("member") => {
            let prop = obj["prop"].as_str().expect("validated");
            let base_name = obj["obj"]["name"].as_str().expect("validated");
            let Some(base) = scope.get(base_name) else {
                return decline(format!("unbound identifier '{base_name}'"));
            };
            match base.get(prop) {
                Some(v) => Ok(v.clone()),
                None => decline(format!("'{base_name}' has no field '{prop}'")),
            }
        }
        Some("template") => {
            let parts = obj["parts"].as_array().expect("validated");
            let mut out = String::new();
            for part in parts {
                match part.get("kind").and_then(Value::as_str) {
                    Some("text") => out.push_str(part["s"].as_str().expect("validated")),
                    Some("expr") => {
                        let value = eval_ir(&part["e"], scope, input)?;
                        match value {
                            Value::String(s) => out.push_str(&s),
                            other => {
                                return decline(format!(
                                    "template part evaluated to non-string {other}; \
                                     templates are string-only in this version \
                                     (gnexec would stringify — decline, not diverge)"
                                ))
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    _ => return decline("unreachable: validated template part"),
                }
            }
            Ok(Value::String(out))
        }
        _ => decline("unreachable: validated IR kind"),
    }
}

#[cfg(test)]
mod unit_tests {
    use super::*;

    fn topo(json: &str) -> Topology {
        serde_json::from_str(json).expect("test topology parses")
    }

    #[test]
    fn envelope_requires_exact_keys() {
        assert!(run_envelope_bytes(b"{\"topology\":{\"nodes\":[],\"edges\":[]}}").is_err());
        assert!(run_envelope_bytes(b"not json").is_err());
        assert!(run_envelope_bytes(
            br#"{"topology":{"nodes":[],"edges":[]},"input":{},"extra":1}"#
        )
        .is_err());
        // v2 shape must be exactly topology+helpers+input.
        assert!(run_envelope_bytes(
            br#"{"topology":{"nodes":[],"edges":[]},"helpers":{},"input":{},"extra":1}"#
        )
        .is_err());
        // helpers must be an object.
        assert!(run_envelope_bytes(
            br#"{"topology":{"nodes":[],"edges":[]},"helpers":[],"input":{}}"#
        )
        .is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn empty_topology_declines() {
        let t = topo(r#"{"nodes":[],"edges":[]}"#);
        assert!(run_topology(&t, &Value::Null).is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn unknown_edge_type_declines() {
        let t = topo(
            r#"{"nodes":[
                 {"id":"e","labels":["Entry"],"properties":{}},
                 {"id":"r","labels":["Return"],"properties":{"expr":"'x'"}}],
               "edges":[
                 {"source_ids":["e"],"target_ids":["r"],"type":"Race","properties":{}}]}"#,
        );
        let err = run_topology(&t, &Value::Null).unwrap_err();
        assert!(err.0.contains("Race"), "unexpected: {err}");
    }

    #[test]
    fn literal_return_walks() {
        let t = topo(
            r#"{"nodes":[
                 {"id":"e","labels":["Entry"],"properties":{}},
                 {"id":"r","labels":["Return"],"properties":{"expr":"'hi'"}}],
               "edges":[
                 {"source_ids":["e"],"target_ids":["r"],"type":"Process","properties":{}}]}"#,
        );
        assert_eq!(
            run_topology(&t, &Value::Null).unwrap(),
            Value::String("hi".into())
        );
    }

    #[test]
    fn input_field_return_walks() {
        let t = topo(
            r#"{"nodes":[
                 {"id":"e","labels":["Entry"],"properties":{}},
                 {"id":"r","labels":["Return"],"properties":{"expr":"input.name"}}],
               "edges":[
                 {"source_ids":["e"],"target_ids":["r"],"type":"Process","properties":{}}]}"#,
        );
        let input: Value = serde_json::from_str(r#"{"name":"ada"}"#).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(
            run_topology(&t, &input).unwrap(),
            Value::String("ada".into())
        );
        // missing field → decline
        assert!(run_topology(&t, &serde_json::json!({})).is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn unknown_ir_kind_declines() {
        let mut scope = BTreeMap::new();
        scope.insert("x".to_string(), Value::Null);
        assert!(eval_expr(r#"{"kind":"binary","op":"+"}"#, &scope, &Value::Null).is_err());
        assert!(eval_expr("a + b", &scope, &Value::Null).is_err());
        assert!(eval_expr("input.a.b", &scope, &Value::Null).is_err());
        // call IR is statement-level only, never expression-level.
        assert!(eval_expr(
            r#"{"kind":"call","callee":"f","args":[]}"#,
            &scope,
            &Value::Null
        )
        .is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn template_ir_concatenates_strings_only() {
        let mut scope = BTreeMap::new();
        scope.insert("name".to_string(), Value::String("x".into()));
        let expr = r#"{"kind":"template","parts":[{"kind":"text","s":"hello:"},{"kind":"expr","e":{"kind":"ident","name":"name"}}]}"#;
        assert_eq!(
            eval_expr(expr, &scope, &Value::Null).unwrap(),
            Value::String("hello:x".into())
        );
        // Non-string ref traps (gnexec would stringify; decline, not diverge).
        scope.insert("name".to_string(), Value::Number(5.into()));
        let err = eval_expr(expr, &scope, &Value::Null).unwrap_err();
        assert!(err.0.contains("non-string"), "{err}");
        // Unbound ref traps.
        scope.remove("name");
        assert!(eval_expr(expr, &scope, &Value::Null).is_err());
    }

    #[test]
    fn member_ir_reads_bound_object_fields() {
        let mut scope = BTreeMap::new();
        scope.insert(
            "input".to_string(),
            serde_json::json!({"name": "ada"}),
        );
        let expr = r#"{"kind":"member","obj":{"kind":"ident","name":"input"},"prop":"name"}"#;
        assert_eq!(
            eval_expr(expr, &scope, &Value::Null).unwrap(),
            Value::String("ada".into())
        );
        // Missing field → decline.
        scope.insert("input".to_string(), serde_json::json!({}));
        assert!(eval_expr(expr, &scope, &Value::Null).is_err());
        // Unbound base → decline.
        scope.remove("input");
        assert!(eval_expr(expr, &scope, &Value::Null).is_err());
        // Deep member chains are outside the subset.
        let deep = r#"{"kind":"member","obj":{"kind":"member","obj":{"kind":"ident","name":"a"},"prop":"b"},"prop":"c"}"#;
        assert!(eval_expr(deep, &scope, &Value::Null).is_err());
    }
}
